        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You grew up in a Bratovitch family in Lithuanian long in the service of the Tzimisce.  Vampiric blood flowed through your veins at birth and you would have served in the hellhound kennels on your Voivode's estate.  Unfortunately this was not to be.  The Anarchs came and burned your Master's manse to the ground and you fled with him and a few other survivors across the sea to New York.   There you were safe for a time with your Master, from the Camarilla and the Sabbat.  When your Master succumbed to Torpor most of your family abandoned him to seek out new lords among the Sabbat.  You and a few of your brothers stayed loyal and even went so far as o hunt vampires in hopes of finding blood to awaken your Master.  While you were unable to wake him with these offerings, you soon became addicted to the vitae that you stole from these vampires you  hunted with your brothers.  As your lust for this blood grew you began to plot your Master's demise.  When you were finally able to drink his heart's blood you felt changed in a way you didn't expect.  When your brothers turned on you for killing their Master, your undead flesh ignored their blows and you pulled the flesh from their bones with unlearned ease.  For a time you continued to hide from the Camarilla and the Sabbat, but the Blood of the Labyrinth found you.  Your vampire hunting skills endeared you to Abigail and you even destroyed a Sabbat Inquisitor to prove to her and Alabastor you were worthy to join the them.  Other Sabbat do not know you never underwent the Creation Rites and consider you a True Sabbat. Only Alabastor and Abigail know both of your secrets."
        ],
        [
